An exciting weekend is planned for participants in the national finals of the 2022 World Corporate Golf Challenge (WCGC) as soft drink brand, Pepsi and the favourite brand on the stable of Guinness Nigeria, Singleton; join the prestigious class of WCGC sponsors. WCGC is the largest World Corporate Golf Tournament in the world and Falcon Golf Development Company (Falcon Golf) is the events franchise holder in Nigeria.   Knocks trail Nigeria’s withdrawal from global…     Dessers wins club Player of the Month award     NBBF to get Interim Management Committee   While Pepsi is offering their celebrity disc jockey, DJ Scratch, and the renowned Storm Band to cool the evenings with light music, Guinness is providing Singleton single malt whiskey to make the 2022 WCGC an event to remember. Billed for the serene Lakowe Lakes Golf and Country Estate in Lagos from May 20th to May 22nd, “the national finals is a must-play for discerning golfers”, says Remi Olukoya, the Chief Executive Officer of Falcon Golf, a pioneer Nigerian brand in golf course development in Nigeria. “It’s going to be WCGC with a difference, a unique tournament reminiscent of the world finals itself”, Olukoya explains, adding that, “this event is not an event any golfer should miss! We are going to offer value for every penny spent in this event so both sponsors and players are in for a great outing.”